<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="152" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d152">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 857.857/82</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Havre</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Osborne</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Havre</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-23">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 23, 1917</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 4 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Norwegian steamer <hi rend="italic">Skrim</hi>, unarmed, proceeding
                                in ballast from Tréport to Cardiff, was sunk by bombs by German
                                submarine, after warning, February 19, 20 miles from Tréport. Crew
                                14 including Porto Rican, Louis Pinto, were in lifeboats about 20
                                hours. Depositions captain and Pinto taken.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Osborne</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>